description: Test (measure voltage across) the switched cables indicator LED in the sensor module during the normal 'on' cycle and during the brief 'off' cycle, to determine if the LED follows the same on/off behavior as the lamp. This will identify if the relay is actually opening or if the issue lies downstream., outcome='All voltage measurements at the various control panel components and cables were completed successfully after opening the inspection panel. No polarity inversion was detected in any of the measured cables. The Control Input Cable (+) measured at approximately 12\u202fV, and the Control Input Cable (−) was near 0\u202fV, while the Control Output Cable (+) was at 0.36\u202fV, and the Control Output Cable (−) remained near 0\u202fV.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=205.0, cost_breakdown=[('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('open_inspection_panel', 5.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Observe -> switched cables indicator LED (sensor module),
description: Visually inspect the switched cables indicator LED in the sensor module during the brief interval when the load lamp is off, to determine if the LED turns off or stays lit. This will verify if the power interruption is occurring at the relay or further downstream., outcome='The requested action could not be mapped to any recognized diagnostic operation. Only actions from the available action list are supported (e.g. measure_voltage, test_continuity, inspect_connections, verify_repair, …).\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=0.0, cost_breakdown=[], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Observe -> Ambient light sensor module (relay),
description: Visually inspect the relay inside the ambient sensor module during the brief lamp-off interval. Determine whether the relay is physically opening during the lamp-off event, which would indicate active switching, or whether it remains closed (indicating the fault is downstream or in the relay drive circuit)., outcome='Diagnostic result: The control relay was observed and remains physically closed during the lamp-off event. There is no observable internal fault in the relay.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=15.0, cost_breakdown=[('open_inspection_panel', 5.0), ('observe_component', 10.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> Switched cables indicator LED (sensor module) - current measurement,
description: Measure the current through the switched cables indicator LED in the ambient sensor module during both the 'on' and brief 'off' intervals of the load lamp. This will determine if the actual current path is being intermittently interrupted at the indicator/detection point, revealing if load current is shut off upstream of the lamp module., outcome='The measured current through the PSU Status LED (green) is 0.010696 A. No interruption in current is reported at this measurement point.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=20.0, cost_breakdown=[('measure_current', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Observe -> Ambient sensor module switched cables output terminals,
description: Visually inspect the four cable terminals on the ambient sensor module during the lamp-off interval for signs of arcing, overheating, intermittent contact, or loose terminals. This can help determine if a mechanical connection issue is intermittently interrupting continuity despite prior resistance tests., outcome='All four cable terminals on the ambient sensor module were visually inspected, with no signs of arcing, overheating, intermittent contact, or loose terminals observed. No observable internal faults were detected in any of the cables. No polarity inversion was detected during this inspection.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=40.0, cost_breakdown=[('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> Control Module (potentiometer sensitivity adjustment circuit),
description: Test the sensitivity potentiometer by adjusting it through its full range while monitoring the lamp's cycling behavior. This will determine if the sensitivity setting is causing the relay to pulse at intervals or if it is stuck in a near-threshold condition, resulting in periodic toggling., outcome='The sensitivity potentiometer was successfully adjusted through its full range, from 0.50 to 0.00 and then from 0.00 to 1.00. The action steps completed without errors; the potentiometer responded as expected.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=40.0, cost_breakdown=[('adjust_potentiometer', 20.0), ('adjust_potentiometer', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> Power Supply Module (battery voltage under load),
description: Test the voltage of the 12V battery under load during both the lamp-on and lamp-off intervals. This will identify whether the battery voltage sags or fluctuates, possibly causing the periodic lamp shutdown despite normal module operation., outcome='Voltage measurement at the battery shows 12.0 V on the positive terminal and 0.0 V on the negative terminal. No polarity inversion is detected at the measurement points.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=30.0, cost_breakdown=[('invert_enclosure', 10.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> Switched cables indicator LED (sensor module) - voltage across LED/resistor during lamp-off event,
description: Measure the voltage across both the switched cables indicator LED and its series resistor in the ambient sensor module during the lamp-off event. This will help determine if current to both the indicator and the load is being interrupted at the same moment, distinguishing between a load-side and a control-side intermittent disconnect., outcome='The measured voltages indicate 1.2916 V at the LED anode (0.0 V cathode), and the series resistor shows 11.99 V on one terminal and 1.29 V on the other. No polarity inversion is observed for these measurements.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=40.0, cost_breakdown=[('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Observe -> Control module (internal circuit board and relay drive circuit),
description: Visually inspect the internal circuit board within the control module, especially around the relay coil, relay contacts, and drive circuitry. Look for intermittent faults such as cold solder joints, cracked PCB traces, or loose relay contacts that might cause brief periodic disconnection despite the relay appearing closed and powered., outcome='All inspected components—the control relay, ambient light sensor, sensitivity potentiometer, timing potentiometer, and sensor bias resistor—show no observable internal faults. The relay is confirmed closed, and all visual inspections were completed successfully without detecting visible issues. No intermittent faults such as cold solder joints, cracked PCB traces, or loose relay contacts were observed.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=55.0, cost_breakdown=[('open_inspection_panel', 5.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0)], simplified_outcome=None)] 
